Then $\angle BIC = 180^\circ - \frac{\angle A}{2} - \frac{\angle C}{2} = 180^\circ - \frac{1}{2} \cdot 70^\circ - \frac{1}{2} \cdot 110^\circ = 70^\circ.$  Then $\angle BRC = 180^\circ - \angle BIC = 110^\circ.$

Since $\angle BRC = 110^\circ,$ $\angle BPC = 70^\circ.$  Then $\triangle BPQ$ is a 30-40-50 triangle, so $BQ = 40$ and $PQ = 30.$

By the Law of Cosines on triangle $BRQ,$
\[y^2 = BQ^2 + QR^2 - 2 \cdot BQ \cdot QR \cdot \cos \angle BQR = 40^2 + 30^2 - 2 \cdot 40 \cdot 30 \cdot \cos 70^\circ.\]By the Law of Cosines on triangle $APR,$
\[x^2 = AP^2 + PQ^2 - 2 \cdot AP \cdot PQ \cdot \cos \angle APQ = (AD - DP)^2 + PQ^2 - 2 (AD - DP) PQ \cdot \cos 70^\circ.\]Since $AD = 110$ and $DP = PR - DR = PR - BC = x - 90,$
\begin{align*}
x^2 &= (110 - x + 90)^2 + 30^2 - 2 (110 - x + 90) \cdot 30 \cdot \cos 70^\circ \\
&= 400 + 400x - 2 \cdot 30 \cdot (200 - x) \cdot \cos 70^\circ \\
&= 400 + 400x - 12000 \cos 70^\circ + 60x \cos 70^\circ.
\end{align*}Then
\begin{align*}
x^2 - y^2 &= 400 + 400x - 12000 \cos 70^\circ + 60x \cos 70^\circ - (40^2 + 30^2 - 2 \cdot 40 \cdot 30 \cdot \cos 70^\circ) \\
&= 400x + 12000 \cos 70^\circ - 1200 \\
&= 400 (x + 30) + 12000 (\cos 70^\circ - 1) \\
&= 400 (x + 30) - 24000 \sin^2 35^\circ \\
&= 400 (x + 30) - 12000 (1 - \cos 70^\circ) \\
&= 400 (x + 30) - 24000 \sin^2 35^\circ \\
&= 400 (x + 30) - 12000 \sin^2 55^\circ \\
&= 400 (x + 30) - 6000 (1 - \cos 110^\circ) \\
&= 400 (x + 30) + 6000 \cos 110^\circ - 6000 \\
&= 400 (x + 30) + 6000 \cos (-70^\circ) - 6000 \\
&= 400 (x + 30) - 6000 \cos 70^\circ - 6000 \\
&= 400 (x + 30) - 12000 \cos 70^\circ \\
&= 400 (x + 30) - 24000 \sin^2 35^\circ.
\end{align*}Since $\sin^2 35^\circ = \frac{1 - \cos 70^\circ}{2} = \frac{1}{2} - \frac{\sqrt{3}}{4},$
\[|x - y| = \boxed{12}.\]

