C = (6,1);
D = (4.25,3);
H = extension(A, foot(B,A,C), B, foot(A,B,C));
P = extension(D, D + (C - B), A, B);
Q = extension(D, D + (B - C), A, C);

draw(A--B--C--cycle);
draw(A--H);
draw(B--H);
draw(C--H);
draw(D--P);
draw(D--Q);
draw(B--foot(B,A,C));
draw(A--foot(A,B,C));
draw((0,20/3)--(20,20/3),dashed);

label("$A$", A, N);
label("$B$", B, SW);
label("$C$", C, SE);
label("$D$", D, NE);
label("$H$", H, S);
label("$P$", P, S);
label("$Q$", Q, E, UnFill);
[/asy]

The line $y = -\frac{1}{3} x + \frac{20}{3}$ intersects the line $AB,$ which has equation $y = \frac{5}{2} - \frac{3}{2} x,$ at $P = \left( \frac{10}{7}, \frac{30}{7} \right).$  The line $y = -\frac{1}{3} x + \frac{20}{3}$ intersects the line $AC,$ which has equation $y = \frac{1}{3} x + \frac{29}{3},$ at $Q = \left( 3, 6 \right).$

